  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "start_char": 0,
      "end_char": 54,
      "summary": "To solve this problem, we'll break it down into steps.",
      "step_type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "start_char": 56,
      "end_char": 135,
      "summary": "**Step 1: Determine the total number of outcomes when flipping a coin 4 times**",
      "step_type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "start_char": 137,
      "end_char": 264,
      "summary": "Since each flip has two possible outcomes (heads or tails), and there are four flips in total, the total number of ou...",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "start_char": 266,
      "end_char": 284,
      "summary": "2 \u00d7 2 \u00d7 2 \u00d7 2 = 16",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "start_char": 286,
      "end_char": 355,
      "summary": "**Step 2: Find the number of ways to get exactly 2 heads in 4 flips**",
      "step_type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "start_char": 357,
      "end_char": 535,
      "summary": "We can use combinations to calculate this. The formula for combinations is nCr = n! / (r!(n-r)!), where n is the tota...",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "start_char": 537,
      "end_char": 597,
      "summary": "In our case, we want to choose 2 out of 4 flips to be heads:",
      "step_type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "start_char": 599,
      "end_char": 624,
      "summary": "4C2 = 4! / (2!(4-2)!) = 6",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "start_char": 626,
      "end_char": 681,
      "summary": "So, there are 6 ways to get exactly 2 heads in 4 flips.",
      "step_type": "conclusion"
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "start_char": 683,
      "end_char": 756,
      "summary": "**Step 3: Find the number of outcomes where at least one flip is a head**",
      "step_type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "start_char": 758,
      "end_char": 914,
      "summary": "Since we're given that at least one flip was heads, we can exclude the cases where all flips are tails (i.e., 0 heads...",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s12",
      "start_char": 916,
      "end_char": 925,
      "summary": "1 outcome",
      "step_type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "id": "s13",
      "start_char": 927,
      "end_char": 993,
      "summary": "Now, subtract this from the total number of outcomes: 16 - 1 = 15",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s14",
      "start_char": 995,
      "end_char": 1055,
      "summary": "So, there are 15 outcomes where at least one flip is a head.",
      "step_type": "conclusion"
    },
    {
      "id": "s15",
      "start_char": 1057,
      "end_char": 1155,
      "summary": "**Step 4: Find the probability of getting exactly 2 heads given that at least one flip was heads**",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s16",
      "start_char": 1157,
      "end_char": 1248,
      "summary": "We want to find P(exactly 2 heads | at least 1 head). To do this, we'll use Bayes' theorem:",
      "step_type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "id": "s17",
      "start_char": 1250,
      "end_char": 1271,
      "summary": "P(A|B) = P(AB) / P(B)",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s18",
      "start_char": 1273,
      "end_char": 1396,
      "summary": "In our case, A is the event of getting exactly 2 heads (6 outcomes), and B is the event of at least one head (15 outc...",
      "step_type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "id": "s19",
      "start_char": 1398,
      "end_char": 1567,
      "summary": "We need to find P(AB), which is the probability of both events occurring. Since we're given that at least one flip wa...",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s20",
      "start_char": 1569,
      "end_char": 1656,
      "summary": "P(AB) = Number of outcomes with exactly 2 heads and at least one head = 6 (from Step 2)",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s21",
      "start_char": 1658,
      "end_char": 1742,
      "summary": "Now, plug in the values: P(exactly 2 heads | at least 1 head) = P(AB) / P(B) = 6/15",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s22",
      "start_char": 1744,
      "end_char": 1773,
      "summary": "Simplify the fraction: = 2/5",
      "step_type": "derivation"
    },
    {
      "id": "s23",
      "start_char": 1775,
      "end_char": 1882,
      "summary": "Therefore, the probability of getting exactly 2 heads, given that at least one flip was a head, is **2/5**.",
      "step_type": "conclusion"
    }
